# Protect KillerScan arming

Neighborhood poll + ambient notice arming is proven via **Killer Orchestrator** (`ArmRuntimeLoops` → sole `StartKillerScanLoop`, re-arm before tick body). **Do not modify** unless the user explicitly asks.

## Frozen surface

- `ArmRuntimeLoops`, `ScheduleBootArm` (deadline), `EnsurePlayerCombatQuest`
- `StartKillerScanLoop` / KillerScan `OnTimer` (re-arm **before** tick body; busy-skip must not block re-arm)
- `HandleGameResume` / `HandlePlayerLoadFromAlias` / alias `OnPlayerLoadGame`
- Main `OnInit` / `OnQuestInit` arming calls into the above

## Allowed nearby work

- Filter / toast / fixation / line-bank changes that do **not** edit arming
- Additive listener calls from KillerScan dispatch

## Not allowed without permission

- Reintroducing feature `StartTimer` loops (hunger/bond/trust/notice/boot/decay nudge)
- Removing load re-arm / PlayerCombat start
- Putting risky natives on the KillerScan hot path before re-arm
- Bringing back `WorldScan` as a second orchestrator
